In order to compare the current risk classification SVS/MH with the results of the BHM, we computed the posterior estimates of the ‘exceedence’ probability of risk Prob (θit > 1) ∣ y [20–22] further categorized into 4 categories (0, 1, 2, 3) if Prob(θit > 1) assumed < 0.5, 0.5–0.75, 0.75–0.95 and >  0.95, respectively. Exceedence categories were compared with the four SVS/MH risk classes via the weighted Kappa correlation test. Finally, the correspondent three-year moving average of the annual number of cases per municipality predicted by the model BHM (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
